        "paragraphs" : [
            {
                "type" : "WYSIWYG",
                "content" : "<p>The <a href='https://www.nature.com/articles/sdata201618'>FAIR principles</a> are a concept which originated in data management. The acronym stands for Findable, Accessible, Interoperable and Reusable. They have served as a flagship for promoting good data management practices, but <a href='https://dx.doi.org/10.3233/DS-190026'>until recently</a> they were not directly applicable to software. We hope that the FAIR principles will have a positive effect in research software development.</p>"
